    • Energy

    • Energy

      public Energy(SampledInterval bounds, CalibrationStatus calibration, List<EnergyBand> energyBands, Integer dimension, Double resolvingPower, Interval resolvingPowerBounds, Double resolution, Interval resolutionBounds, Double sampleSize, String bandpassName, EnergyTransition transition, Double restwav)
      full parameter constructor.
      Parameters:
      bounds - energy bounds that include the data (barycentric vacuum wavelength).
      calibration - term describing the calibration of the energy axis values.
      energyBands - standard name of the energy regime(s) included in the data (attribute name and cardinality changed in CAOM-2.4).
      dimension - number of measurements (pixels) on the energy axis.
      resolvingPower - mean spectral resolving power per pixel (relative resolution).
      resolvingPowerBounds - range of resolving power within the bounds (relative resolution).
      resolution - mean absolute spectral resolution per pixel.
      resolutionBounds - range of absolute spectral resolution within the bounds.
      sampleSize - mean pixel size.
      bandpassName - telescope- and instrument-specific name for the energy band included.
      transition - target energy transition for this data.
      restwav - rest wavelength of the target energy transition.
